urls.description: Michigan State Police confirmed Thursday they are investigating how election ballots for Florence Township ended up on the side of the road. St. Joseph County Clerk Lindsay Oswald said Thursday the ballots were for the March primary election and were supposed to arrive at Florence Township Clerk Allissa Bowers's home Jan. 21. She said it wasn't until Jan. 29 Bowers notified Oswald she was not in possession of the ballots. Oswald said the county reordered new ballots immediately.
urls.title: Ballots found in the road after being delivered to Florence Township Clerk
